American jurisprudence,

14:33.394 --> 14:37.920
the rich and the famous
do not end up in jail, okay?

14:38.486 --> 14:39.966
[ Door opens ]

14:40.009 --> 14:41.576
I guess all I need
to be is rich, then.

14:41.619 --> 14:43.621
Jesus Christ.

14:43.665 --> 14:45.145
You should
lock your door.

14:45.188 --> 14:47.582
There's trouble afoot.
Have you not seen the news?

14:47.625 --> 14:49.279
How'd you find out
where we live?

14:49.323 --> 14:51.412
[ Scoffs ]

14:51.455 --> 14:53.109
That's your question?

14:53.153 --> 14:56.156
Not how I'm walking,
how I'm talking?

14:56.199 --> 14:58.462
You want to know
how I found your address?

14:58.506 --> 15:00.725
[ Scoffs ] This guy.

15:00.769 --> 15:02.597
My God.
It's incredible.

15:02.640 --> 15:05.469
[ Taser crackles ]Ta-da.

15:05.513 --> 15:07.819
Y-You're vocal cords.

15:07.863 --> 15:09.038
I know.

15:09.082 --> 15:10.387
It's amazing
what you can do

15:10.431 --> 15:12.259
when you put
your mind to it.

15:12.302 --> 15:15.088
Hey, you must have been able to
vocalize in the hospital.

15:15.131 --> 15:16.785
How about I take
the pop quiz another time?

15:16.828 --> 15:17.786
I'm having a day.

15:17.829 --> 15:18.743
[ Taser crackles ]Sit down.

15:18.787 --> 15:20.615
Okay, okay.

15:24.880 --> 15:27.535
My God, you're
actually back.

15:27.578 --> 15:29.058
You're really you.

15:29.102 --> 15:32.192
In form.

15:32.235 --> 15:35.586
Not in substance.

15:35.630 --> 15:37.371
What did you do to me?

15:37.414 --> 15:38.241
What do you mean?

15:38.285 --> 15:39.895
I mean
I'm not who I was.

15:39.939 --> 15:41.636
I feel changed.

15:41.679 --> 15:42.985
What have you done?

15:43.029 --> 15:44.944
What have I done?

15:44.987 --> 15:48.077
I healed you.
I-I saved your life.

15:48.121 --> 15:50.862
You operated
on my head.

15:50.906 --> 15:52.995
Did you give me
a lobotomy or...?

15:53.039 --> 15:56.303
No, no, I-I relieved
some cranial pressure,

15:56.346 --> 15:57.391
some bleeding.

15:57.434 --> 16:00.437
You're lying.

16:00.481 --> 16:02.613
I feel different.

16:02.657 --> 16:05.660
Okay, different how?

16:05.703 --> 16:09.446
Mentally,
I feel...weaker.

16:09.490 --> 16:12.841
I...I feel...

16:15.104 --> 16:17.237
...regret.

16:17.280 --> 16:19.021
Regret?

16:19.065 --> 16:20.805
For the things
I've done.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.416
I've never
felt that before.

16:22.459 --> 16:23.721
I don't like it.

16:23.765 --> 16:25.114
It's a weakness.

16:27.247 --> 16:31.294
M-Maybe I inadvertently
gave you a conscience.

16:31.338 --> 16:32.339
[ Taser crackles ]Don't gloat.

16:32.382 --> 16:34.341
I...

16:34.384 --> 16:37.344
Did you snip something
in my brain?

16:37.387 --> 16:39.999
No, no, I swear.
I swear.

16:40.042 --> 16:43.785
I was just something to
experiment on, huh?

16:43.828 --> 16:46.962
Okay.
I'll give you that.

16:47.006 --> 16:51.488
But I did not alter
your brain, okay?

16:51.532 --> 16:53.055
Don't stare at me.

16:53.099 --> 16:55.057
I'm not a zoo monkey.

16:55.101 --> 17:00.062
No. No, you're...
you're a miracle.

17:00.106 --> 17:03.544
You find me
attractive, Cora?

17:03.587 --> 17:05.372
Huh?

17:05.415 --> 17:07.548
What type of person
flirts with a man

17:07.591 --> 17:09.898
in a vegetative
state, huh?

17:12.161 --> 17:16.078
Huh?
[ Gasps ]

17:16.122 --> 17:17.732
How do you -- How do you
remember that?

17:17.775 --> 17:22.215
Oh, I remember
every second.

17:22.258 --> 17:25.957
It was the highlight
of my month.

17:30.527 --> 17:32.660
Have you -- Have you been
conscious this whole time?

17:32.703 --> 17:34.618
In and out.

17:34.662 --> 17:37.056
It's complicated.

17:39.884 --> 17:42.409
Wait, so we're closing
the business?

17:42.452 --> 17:44.237
For now.

17:44.280 --> 17:45.412
And you should
probably seek

17:45.455 --> 17:46.891
other living
accommodations.

17:46.935 --> 17:48.023
Like hell.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.024
Ida.

17:49.068 --> 17:52.245
I'm not moving
out of my house.

17:52.288 --> 17:54.856
I have my routines.

17:54.899 --> 17:57.076
Plus which,
he's not gonna bother me.

17:57.119 --> 17:59.295
Yeah, what makes
you think that?

17:59.339 --> 18:02.429
I bought ice cream cones
off the man for years.

18:02.472 --> 18:05.867
I was always
unfailingly courteous.

18:05.910 --> 18:07.956
What goes around
comes around.

18:07.999 --> 18:09.566
You might want
to remember that, Bill.

18:09.610 --> 18:11.438
Yeah, well, you might want
to remember that

18:11.481 --> 18:15.485
what comes 'round for me
might happily settle for you!

18:15.529 --> 18:19.098
Killing people I care about
is his idea of a hobby!

18:19.141 --> 18:21.100
And it's people
you love.

18:23.276 --> 18:24.842
People I love.

18:28.063 --> 18:33.024
Isn't it more likely that
maybe he was removed?

18:33.068 --> 18:34.722
I mean, maybe the doctor
just moved him

18:34.765 --> 18:37.638
to another place
to continue the experiment.

18:37.681 --> 18:39.466
Hodges: I saw
the security footage.

18:39.509 --> 18:41.163
That didn't happen.

18:41.207 --> 18:43.600
Okay, well, how likely is it
that he wakes up...

18:43.644 --> 18:46.516
Why the fuck is everybody
stuck on this "likely"?

18:46.560 --> 18:49.780
Can we just agree there is no
such thing as fucking "likely"?

18:49.824 --> 18:51.913
It doesn't exist, okay?

18:51.956 --> 18:53.828
Okay.

18:53.871 --> 18:56.309
We're not the enemy.

18:56.352 --> 18:58.267
You all need to be
vigilant, okay?

18:58.311 --> 18:59.399
That's all I'm saying.

18:59.442 --> 19:01.531
And make yourselves
scarce.

19:01.575 --> 19:03.838
Finders Keepers
is closed for now.

19:03.881 --> 19:04.795
And you can't be living
with me until

19:04.839 --> 19:05.796
this whole thing
is resolved.

19:05.840 --> 19:08.147
That's it.

19:08.190 --> 19:10.801
Sooner you get your ass
back up to Harvard, the better.

19:10.845 --> 19:12.716
Come on, let's go.
We got to go.

19:12.760 --> 19:15.023
[ Keys jingle ]

19:15.066 --> 19:16.111
What about Donna?

19:16.155 --> 19:17.417
Ah, fuck. She's okay.

19:17.460 --> 19:18.722
She's in Seattle,
thanks to God.

19:18.766 --> 19:20.463
She's with Allie.

19:21.682 --> 19:25.207
You know, there's, like, a net
over the whole town, right?

19:25.251 --> 19:26.077
I mean, what --
what's he gonna do?

19:26.121 --> 19:27.601
Where's he gonna go?

19:27.644 --> 19:30.952
Jerome, the man has a knack
for defying the odds.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.650
Or has that escaped you?

19:35.783 --> 19:37.001
[ Grunts ]

19:37.045 --> 19:39.134
[ Sniffs ]

19:39.178 --> 19:42.572
As long as I'm alive
and offering

19:42.616 --> 19:48.056
such medical promise
to the world, you're okay.

19:49.579 --> 19:55.237
But if I die, all your
experimentation goes for naught.

19:55.281 --> 19:57.935
Your public image...

19:57.979 --> 20:02.288
So we, each of us,
have a vested interest...

20:02.331 --> 20:04.899
[ Taser crackles ]...in my continued good health.

20:10.034 --> 20:11.253
Agreed?

20:11.297 --> 20:12.602
Yeah.
Yes.

20:12.646 --> 20:14.865
Okay.

20:14.909 --> 20:17.781
So, what's
the prognosis, Doc?

20:21.307 --> 20:26.225
Um...first, we need to get you
back to a hospital.

20:26.268 --> 20:28.836
The drug you're on
is called Cerebellin.

20:28.879 --> 20:32.492
It's temporary as much as
it is miraculous.

20:32.535 --> 20:35.190
You'll need another dose
within three days.

20:35.234 --> 20:37.584
Or...?

20:37.627 --> 20:40.108
I don't want
to speculate.

20:40.151 --> 20:41.805
Or?

20:41.849 --> 20:45.287
You'll weaken
and most likely die.

20:45.331 --> 20:51.337
The regression, when it happens,
it comes on very quick.

20:51.380 --> 20:54.253
Now, there's -- there's
also side effects.

20:54.296 --> 20:56.124
Such as?

20:56.167 --> 21:02.478
I-I-In lab animals,
mostly, uh, glioblastomas.

21:04.263 --> 21:05.873
Brain tumors.

21:05.916 --> 21:08.136
Yes. Y-You need
to have continued injections

21:08.179 --> 21:10.138
of Cerebellin
inside the cortex.

21:10.181 --> 21:12.401
And this -- this -- this
drug supply, where is it?

21:12.445 --> 21:13.576
The hospital?

21:13.620 --> 21:15.839
Uh, some.
It's mainly in China.

21:15.883 --> 21:17.406
It hasn't been
approved here.

21:17.450 --> 21:19.321
Right.

21:19.365 --> 21:24.457
So medically speaking,
I'm a dead man walking.

21:27.242 --> 21:28.983
Fuck.

21:36.904 --> 21:40.821
You know what
we are, us three?

21:43.737 --> 21:47.131
We're a teamie-weamie, okay?

21:47.175 --> 21:49.264
We can each benefit
one another.

21:49.308 --> 21:52.789
Win, win, common good.

21:52.833 --> 21:56.140
You know, that would never have
appealed to me before.

21:56.184 --> 21:58.839
Are you sure
you didn't snip something?

21:58.882 --> 21:59.709
No --Rhetorical.

21:59.753 --> 22:01.145
[ Taser crackles ]Aah!

22:01.189 --> 22:02.756
Okay.
[ Groans ]

22:02.799 --> 22:04.801
Now it's time
we go for a little drive.

22:04.845 --> 22:05.933
What do you mean?

22:05.976 --> 22:08.501
Just a little drive
in your car.

22:08.544 --> 22:11.721
It's nicer than
the one I stole.

22:11.765 --> 22:13.201
What do you say, Cora?

22:13.244 --> 22:16.813
Time for a little
teamie-weamie outing.

22:16.857 --> 22:19.294
[ Taser crackles ]

22:19.338 --> 22:25.169
♪♪

22:25.213 --> 22:26.823
Oh, my God.

22:26.867 --> 22:28.521
Are you packed?

22:28.564 --> 22:32.481
Clearly, I'd be safer here
than in some hotel.

22:32.525 --> 22:34.527
We're not having
that discussion.

22:34.570 --> 22:36.311
[ Gun clicks ]

22:36.355 --> 22:39.314
I've wasted too much
time trying to convince people

22:39.358 --> 22:41.272
of things they're
ill-inclined to accept.

22:41.316 --> 22:42.535
Right.

22:42.578 --> 22:44.363
That chapter
of my life is over.

22:47.496 --> 22:53.415
So, he shows up here,
just boom, right in the head?

22:53.459 --> 22:55.852
To be safe.

22:55.896 --> 22:58.420
The tinsmith didn't
give him a heart.

23:01.118 --> 23:04.818
Oh, hark, I hear
the roar of a lecture.

23:04.861 --> 23:07.603
I don't have
a lecture.

23:07.647 --> 23:11.215
[ Sighs ] No, no word
to the wise, even?

23:11.259 --> 23:13.130
"Bill, don't kill him,
you're better than this"?

23:13.174 --> 23:15.306
I tried to kill him,
too, remember?

23:15.350 --> 23:20.050
I mean, I smashed
his head to bits.

23:20.094 --> 23:22.096
I thought.

23:22.139 --> 23:25.099
And I...I don't feel
bad about that at all,

23:25.142 --> 23:26.796
so, you know.

23:29.320 --> 23:31.888
Okay.

23:35.936 --> 23:38.286
You know, when I got home
that night, I found all these,

23:38.329 --> 23:43.596
um, hard bits of
something on my clothes.

23:43.639 --> 23:47.251
I realized they were
Brady Hartsfield brain pieces.

23:47.295 --> 23:51.212
You know, his thoughts.

23:51.255 --> 23:54.171
And when I washed my clothes,
it felt like all of

23:54.215 --> 23:57.914
his evil ideas were being
washed away because of me.

23:57.958 --> 24:01.918
And I...felt clean.

24:03.529 --> 24:07.881
And the world felt cleaner,
and I liked that feeling a lot.

24:13.190 --> 24:14.540
I don't mind
you cleaning up.

24:14.583 --> 24:18.544
I just don't want
you to get hurt.

24:18.587 --> 24:20.459
[ Groans ]

24:22.678 --> 24:24.550
I won't get hurt.

24:27.161 --> 24:34.560
♪♪

24:34.603 --> 24:42.350
♪♪

24:42.393 --> 24:50.010
♪♪

24:50.053 --> 24:52.926
So we're just gonna
blithely walk in there?

24:52.969 --> 24:55.581
You don't think
they'll be happy to see me?

24:55.624 --> 24:58.453
M-Maybe we should
call ahead first.

24:58.497 --> 25:01.238
What if some young cop
pulls his gun?

25:01.282 --> 25:03.545
They won't even know
who's walked in the door

25:03.589 --> 25:04.894
until I take
these off, okay?

25:04.938 --> 25:06.243
You could get
all three of us shot.

25:06.287 --> 25:07.593
You're being
very negative, Felix.

25:07.636 --> 25:09.116
Can we please just
get this over with?

25:09.159 --> 25:12.119
Wait a second.
Don't rush me.

25:12.162 --> 25:14.600
I don't do my best work
under pressure.

25:16.471 --> 25:18.081
Or maybe I do.

25:18.125 --> 25:19.996
Cora, get in
the back seat, please.

25:22.129 --> 25:23.391
What?Back seat now,

25:23.434 --> 25:25.132
for a second,
before we head in.

25:25.175 --> 25:26.089
Don't do it.

25:26.133 --> 25:27.177
[ Taser crackles ]Excuse me.

25:27.221 --> 25:28.962
Cora, back seat now.Okay.

25:41.017 --> 25:43.106
[ Car door closes ]

25:46.545 --> 25:49.722
I'm not gonna
hurt you.

25:50.940 --> 25:52.942
But I do want
to ask you a favor.

25:56.946 --> 25:58.948
I'd like to kiss you.

26:01.516 --> 26:02.778
Excuse me?

26:05.607 --> 26:07.957
My freedom is over.

26:09.785 --> 26:15.008
I've never been with
an attractive woman before...

26:15.051 --> 26:16.705
other than mother.

26:18.838 --> 26:20.622
Don't ask.

26:22.102 --> 26:27.934
I'm, uh...
I'm 29 years old,

26:27.977 --> 26:31.372
and I've never
been kissed.

26:33.983 --> 26:36.725
How sad is that?

26:37.334 --> 26:41.251
Look, I...I don't...I don't
think that I feel comfortable --

26:41.295 --> 26:44.951
I think we're all a little
out of our comfort zone.

26:44.994 --> 26:46.866
Right, Felix?

26:49.782 --> 26:53.220
I'm not gonna hurt you.

26:55.657 --> 26:57.790
I just want
to know the feeling.

27:02.490 --> 27:04.492
Please.

27:11.020 --> 27:13.196
That was nice,

27:13.240 --> 27:15.503
but not what
I'm talking about.

27:15.546 --> 27:17.810
I need a real kiss.

27:21.204 --> 27:26.253
One that will last
the rest of my life.

27:32.346 --> 27:35.218
Cora, you're going
to be writing a book.

27:35.262 --> 27:36.959
You know this.

27:38.395 --> 27:41.181
"My Day With Mr. Mercedes."

27:42.661 --> 27:44.358
You're gonna
go on the road,

27:44.401 --> 27:48.101
the big junket
to sell that book.

27:50.320 --> 27:53.280
Imagine being able
to talk about

27:53.323 --> 27:57.110
the passionate kiss
you shared with Mr. Mercedes.

27:57.153 --> 28:00.504
That would sell
a lot of books, Cora.

28:02.289 --> 28:04.944
As for me...

28:06.772 --> 28:09.557
...I just want
to know what it feels like.

28:14.388 --> 28:17.130
Please.

28:18.044 --> 28:20.350
Please.

28:43.852 --> 28:47.900
[ Breathing quickens ]

28:53.383 --> 28:57.126
[ Panting ]

28:57.605 --> 28:59.868
Okay, wow.

29:01.087 --> 29:03.089
Now I get it.

29:04.481 --> 29:06.745
You're crying.

29:09.356 --> 29:12.185
Don't put that
in your book.

29:14.448 --> 29:16.624
Okay, teamie.

29:18.495 --> 29:20.236
[ Sniffs ]

29:20.280 --> 29:22.282
Let's go turn
the bad guy in.

29:41.649 --> 29:45.827
[ Indistinct chatter ]

29:47.307 --> 29:48.699
May I help you?

29:48.743 --> 29:51.006
We're here to see Assistant
District Attorney Montez.

29:51.877 --> 29:53.835
Can I tell him
who's asking?

29:53.879 --> 29:56.011
I am.

29:56.055 --> 29:59.145
Heeere's Johnny!

29:59.188 --> 30:00.450
It's Hartsfield.
Put your hands up!

30:00.494 --> 30:02.017
Get on the ground!
Put your hands up!

30:02.061 --> 30:03.932
On the ground!

30:03.976 --> 30:05.891
[ Indistinct shouting ]

30:05.934 --> 30:11.374
♪♪

30:11.418 --> 30:16.858
♪♪

30:16.902 --> 30:19.208
-Back up requested.
-Right there, right there.

30:19.252 --> 30:21.210
♪♪

30:21.254 --> 30:24.387
Little dramatic.

30:24.431 --> 30:27.521
It might be a good thing
that he's out of that hospital.

30:27.564 --> 30:28.739
Well, how do you
figure that?

30:28.783 --> 30:30.785
He was quite
nearly viral.

30:33.701 --> 30:35.877
He was becoming code.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.531
I-I don't even know
what that means.

30:37.574 --> 30:41.230
Um, it means his -- his mind was
fusing with the computers.

30:41.274 --> 30:43.711
Yes! Look, I --
I worked with Brady Hartsfield

30:43.754 --> 30:45.321
for years, and I know
his cyber fingerprint,

30:45.365 --> 30:48.150
and he was in those
fucking monitors,

30:48.194 --> 30:50.457
and he was in these
shitty little handheld devices

30:50.500 --> 30:52.241
that they were
passing around.

30:52.285 --> 30:55.854
I think that he was
in Library Al's Zappit.

31:00.032 --> 31:03.035
Look, uh, Lou,
you might not be safe here.

31:03.078 --> 31:06.908
Do you have a place to stay
till this is resolved?

31:06.952 --> 31:08.997
What, you -- you think
he's gonna --

31:09.041 --> 31:10.825
you think he's gonna
come looking for me?

31:10.869 --> 31:13.219
We can't rule it out.

31:13.262 --> 31:17.136
Maybe I could get
a gun and kill him.

31:18.746 --> 31:21.618
I thought about
killing him in the hospital,

31:21.662 --> 31:24.883
and then I --
and then I didn't.

31:24.926 --> 31:27.363
I didn't have it in me.

31:27.407 --> 31:29.583
Not many people have.

31:29.626 --> 31:31.715
[ Scoffs ]

31:31.759 --> 31:34.327
I didn't think
hehad it in him.

31:34.370 --> 31:36.416
But he did.

31:38.244 --> 31:39.898
I think he really drove
that one home, didn't he?

31:39.941 --> 31:42.552
H-Hey guys.
Guys, look.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.337
Anchor Jeannie: ...walked in
voluntarily and surrendered

31:44.380 --> 31:46.513
himself without incident.

31:46.556 --> 31:49.298
We're told that he was
accompanied by two others.

31:49.342 --> 31:52.084
No confirmed identities,
but we are being told

31:52.127 --> 31:55.826
that one of the persons was
Brady Hartsfield's surgeon.

31:55.870 --> 31:58.090
To repeat, the Mercedes Killer

31:58.133 --> 32:02.224
is in custody after
voluntarily turning himself in.

32:02.268 --> 32:04.444
What?

32:04.487 --> 32:06.054
What?

32:14.236 --> 32:15.324
Hello, sir.

32:15.368 --> 32:16.238
[ Door closes ]

32:16.282 --> 32:18.501
Good to see you
again, Tony.

32:18.545 --> 32:20.155
It is Tony
or Anton?

32:20.199 --> 32:23.245
You know this man?

32:23.289 --> 32:25.987
He kind of tortured me
at the hospital.

32:26.031 --> 32:28.990
Um,
"occupandi temporis."

32:29.034 --> 32:30.992
It sounded like
military talk.

32:34.387 --> 32:36.780
And then you
squeezed my testicles.

32:41.176 --> 32:44.136
I'm not sure why
you did that, sir.

32:51.491 --> 32:54.581
Why are you so upset?

32:54.624 --> 32:56.496
Did I say I was upset?

32:56.539 --> 32:58.106
You don't have to.

32:58.150 --> 33:01.066
You...You look like
you're about to combust.

33:04.547 --> 33:08.290
I mean, he's in custody.
This is a good thing, right?

33:08.334 --> 33:10.205
They got him.

33:16.864 --> 33:19.301
Or was the idea
for you to get him?

